        "inline_data": null,
        "text": "# \ud83d\udfe2 HEARTBEAT_WAKEUP\nYou have been routed ONE isolated task. \n*Task ID*: EPIC-DFP-MOD-ui-gateway\n*Module*: ui-gateway\n*Workdir*: /home/ienliven/Projects/sdlc-factory/workspace/EPIC-DFP-MOD-ui-gateway\n*Phase*: QA_REVIEW\n\n## SYSTEM CONTEXT\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"module_id\": \"ui-gateway\",\n  \"regression_context\": \"No active regression reported.\",\n  \"structural_context\": \"## > BEGIN_ENVIRONMENT\\nStack: Docker Compose, React/Vite (pnpm), Python (uv), PostgreSQL\\nEntry_Point: http://localhost:8000\\nInterface_Mount_Selector: #root\\nINTEGRATION_TEST_CMD: cd ui-gateway && pnpm install && npx playwright install chromium && CI=true npx playwright test --reporter=list\\n## > END_ENVIRONMENT\\n\\n## > BEGIN_MODULE: ui-gateway\\nType: ORCHESTRATOR\\nDescription: The primary entry point for the application. Serves the React SPA, reverse-proxies API requests to `logic-api`, and orchestrates the multi-container environment via `docker-compose.yml`.\\nResponsibilities:\\n- Write `docker-compose.yml` in the project root to orchestrate `ui-gateway`, `logic-api`, and `data-store`.\\n- Implement a React/Vite SPA using Tailwind CSS and `@nivo/heatmap` (or `apexcharts`).\\n- Provide a custom `nginx.conf` to serve the built SPA on port 80 and reverse-proxy `/api/*` to `http://logic-api:8001`.\\n- Map host port 8000 to container port 80.\\n- Implement Playwright E2E tests.\\nRouting Contract:\\n- `docker-compose.yml` routes `ui-gateway` (port 8000:80), `logic-api` (port 8001:8001), and `data-store` (internal network).\\n- Nginx routes `/api/*` to `http://logic-api:8001`.\\n## > END_MODULE: ui-gateway\",\n  \"semantic_context\": \"### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\\n\\n### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\\n\\n### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\",\n  \"memory_insights\": \"No historic pgvector insights found for tester.\"\n}\n```\n\nThe SDLC Protocol and your Playbook are your core instructions.\nCRITICAL: If successful, your handoff JSON must strictly validate against this schema:\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\n    \"status\",\n    \"phase_completed\",\n    \"module_id\",\n    \"all_tests_passed\"\n  ],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"status\": {\n      \"const\": \"success\"\n    },\n    \"phase_completed\": {\n      \"const\": \"QA_REVIEW\"\n    },\n    \"module_id\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\"\n    },\n    \"all_tests_passed\": {\n      \"const\": true\n    },\n    \"failing_tests\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\nIf you learn an architecture-critical lesson, permanently save it for your future self using the native `sdlc_store_memory` tool.\n",
